results.name: Imaginary part of absolute Gaussian perfect numbers, in order of increasing magnitude.
comment: See A102531 for the real part.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..76
mathematica: lst={}; nn=1000; Do[z=a+b*I; If[Abs[z]<=nn && Abs[(DivisorSigma[1, z]-z)] == Abs[z], AppendTo[lst, {Abs[z]^2, z}]], {a, nn}, {b, nn}]; Im[Transpose[Sort[lst]][[2]]]
results.author: _T. D. Noe_, Jan 13 2005
